# Intermediate + Advanced SQL Interview Questions

---

## 1. Find customer names along with total amount spent

```sql id="e7b5tw"
SELECT c.first_name,
       c.last_name,
       SUM(o.amount) AS total_spent
FROM Customers c
JOIN Orders o
ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
GROUP BY c.customer_id, c.first_name, c.last_name;
```

---

## 2. Find the customer who spent the most money

```sql id="5jlwru"
SELECT c.first_name,
       SUM(o.amount) AS total_spent
FROM Customers c
JOIN Orders o
ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
GROUP BY c.customer_id, c.first_name
ORDER BY total_spent DESC
LIMIT 1;
```

---

## 3. Find duplicate ages

```sql id="h5hqng"
SELECT age, COUNT(*) AS total
FROM Customers
GROUP BY age
HAVING COUNT(*) > 1;
```

---

## 4. Find customers who ordered Keyboard

```sql id="0p8f2r"
SELECT c.first_name, c.last_name
FROM Customers c
JOIN Orders o
ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
WHERE o.item = 'Keyboard';
```

---

## 5. Find customers who placed more than one order

```sql id="c5h35r"
SELECT c.first_name,
       COUNT(o.order_id) AS total_orders
FROM Customers c
JOIN Orders o
ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
GROUP BY c.customer_id, c.first_name
HAVING COUNT(o.order_id) > 1;
```

---

## 6. Find the second highest order amount using LIMIT

```sql id="0a7dn8"
SELECT DISTINCT amount
FROM Orders
ORDER BY amount DESC
LIMIT 1 OFFSET 1;
```

---

## 7. Find all customers with Delivered shipping status

```sql id="yzv0xw"
SELECT c.first_name,
       s.status
FROM Customers c
JOIN Shippings s
ON c.customer_id = s.customer
WHERE s.status = 'Delivered';
```

---

## 8. Find all customers who did NOT order anything

```sql id="yoq2n8"
SELECT c.*
FROM Customers c
LEFT JOIN Orders o
ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
WHERE o.order_id IS NULL;
```

---

## 9. Find all items ordered by UK customers

```sql id="kqg6gj"
