       o.item
FROM Customers c
JOIN Orders o
ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
WHERE c.country = 'UK';
```

---

## 10. Count total orders for each item

```sql id="c8qwy5"
SELECT item,
       COUNT(*) AS total_orders
FROM Orders
GROUP BY item;
```

